The paper presents a dynamic data structure for counting subgraphs in graphs with bounded expansion, which is a topic related to graph theory and algorithms. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The paper also involves combinatorial and discrete mathematics, which suggests cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) as another likely category. The paper mentions planar graphs and topological minors, which are topics related to computational geometry, so cs.CG (Computational Geometry) is also a possible category. The paper also involves graph theory and counting, which suggests cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) as another possible category. Finally, the paper involves the analysis of the time complexity of the data structure, which suggests cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) as a possible category.
